 Christianity is an Abrahamic monotheistic religion based on the life and teachings of Jesus of Nazareth. It is the world's largest religion, with about 
2.4 billion followers. [1] Its adherents, known as Christians, make up a majority of the population in 157 countries and territories,[2] and believe that Jesus is the Christ, whose
 coming as the Messiah was prophesied in the Hebrew Bible, called the Old Testament in Christianity, and chronicled in the New Testament.